	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Now hold on.  If you look around multiple boards I post on you will see I constantly and vehimately say "Warriors need help."  You will also constantly see "Do not nerf Knights."  I see Warrior woes as an issue of Warrior functionality.  Where do Knights even figure into the eqaution?  Warrior agro control, which effects their effectiveness as a tank, is in a state of disrepair reguardless if Knights even existed.<br />
<br />
There is this strange idea that if Knights get nerfed, exp groups will run back to Warriors with open arms.  That groups will simply "put up" with Warrior flaky agro control.  Everything I experienced says that many will simply not try.  The only thing nerfing Knights will accomplish is that groups will search for a new method of tanking with solid agro generation.  Whether that is making Rangers tank or using a Beastlord pet or just going without any melee, it will be done much to the dismay of nerf mongering Warriors.<br />
<br />
As far as I can tell, Warriors who scream for nerfs only want to make the low end Knights suffer.  Removing agro from spells will have a consequence for raids which I'm sure most do not consider.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
