	<p>>>Wrong. Monk's shoddy mitiagation means that they take more damage than most other melee classes,<br />
<br />
>>Monks still take more damage than almost any other melee oriented class. Yes, the mitigation nerf was that crippling<br />
<br />
This simply isn't true at the high end game. It starts with VT gear, in elemental/time gear its completely gone. An elemental monk can tank better than any warrior in pre-VT gear in xp groups. I think you underestimate gear/aa. There are monks who could very easily tank King Tormax for example. There are a TON of monks on my server who could offtank a LDoN mob from 100% to 0% hp and not require a single heal. I know I can (bard). And Mend does a hell of alot more than 1500-2000 hp. Buffed well-geared monks have 7k+ hp and crit mend etc.<br />
<br />
I've done groups with vt/ep level players where necro is the primary healer, bard is secondary healer, and monk is MT or offtank.<br />
<br />
>>Classes with better sustained DPS include Necros, Mages, Wizards, Rogues.<br />
>>Classes with equivalent DPS include Rangers, Beastlords, and Warriors.<br />
<br />
In LDoN monks will outdamage wizards, warriors and rangers. Mobs die so frickin fast and are walled constantly that backstab is negligible. Parties move so fast wizards can barely med (and cant use horse). Monks are tied for 3rd best DPS with bst/rog, the 1st/2nd being mag/nec.</p>
	
	
	
	
