	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Originally Posted by <b>Yodelroy</b><br /><i>>>Wrong. Monk's shoddy mitiagation means that they take more damage than most other melee classes,<br />
<br />
>>Monks still take more damage than almost any other melee oriented class. Yes, the mitigation nerf was that crippling<br />
<br />
This simply isn't true at the high end game. It starts with VT gear, in elemental/time gear its completely gone. An elemental monk can tank better than any warrior in pre-VT gear in xp groups. I think you underestimate gear/aa. There are monks who could very easily tank King Tormax for example. There are a TON of monks on my server who could offtank a LDoN mob from 100% to 0% hp and not require a single heal. I know I can (bard). And Mend does a hell of alot more than 1500-2000 hp. Buffed well-geared monks have 7k+ hp and crit mend etc.</i><hr size="1" /></blockquote>Heh, goody... a time geared monk can tank like a Velious geared warrior. Forgive me that's hardy awe-inspiring. <b>Of course</b> monks can tank content that they're ridiculously overpowered for. Hell, a time geared caster can tank LDoN mobs. I've been in groups where it's done. The fact that you need to compare monks with endgame equipment to tanks with gear that's <b>four</b> expansions old proves my point.<br />
<br />
A mend for a monk with 7k hps heals 1750 hit points, exactly in the middle of the range I quoted. A critical mend <b>may</b> happen, but isn't something you can count on, even after spending more than 30 AA points maxxing the ability.<blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />I've done groups with vt/ep level players where necro is the primary healer, bard is secondary healer, and monk is MT or offtank.<hr size="1" /></blockquote>This proves my point, <b>not</b> yours. LDoN mobs are gimpy in comparison to EP mobs. Of course a monk can tank them... so can a shaman, <blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" /><br />
In LDoN monks will outdamage wizards, warriors and rangers. Mobs die so frickin fast and are walled constantly that backstab is negligible. Parties move so fast wizards can barely med (and cant use horse). Monks are tied for 3rd best DPS with bst/rog, the 1st/2nd being mag/nec.<hr size="1" /></blockquote>You need to find better players. Reverse pinning isn't hard, and the speed of kills has no negative impact on rogues. All the rogues I group with get to backstab almost all the time. If they can't, I teach the newbie tank about positioning.<br />
<br />
Wizards with ft15, KEI, 150-ish AAs, and good focus effects do just fine. Sure, they're overpowered for the environment... kinda like the monks that you keep talking up. Even a poorly geared wizard does just fine... hell, a charming chanter can maintain their mana pool easily over the course of an adventure. How do I know? Oh, yeah, I play one.<br />
<br />
You completely neglected to address the point that a well-geared and AAed warrior will do comparable damage to a well-geared and AAed monk, while tanking much better. There's also the matter of rangers, whom you conveniently passed over. A ranger with the right AAs and a good two-hander will do more damage than he will with a bow, putting him right up there in the DPS standings.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
