<tr>
	<td class="alt2" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Kriel Darkbane</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Disciple<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Oct 2001<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Originally Posted by <b>Zorlac Sabboth</b><br /><i><b>What exactly do you want nerfed about bards? </b><br />
- Fading Memories.<br />
<br />
<b>If they've badly designed the elemental planes zones so that bards are the uber pullers all they'd have to do is make a few more mobs immune to lull OR see invisible in the necessary spots. </b><br />
- Has nothing to do with lull. Fading Memories is the core of the problem, hardly limited to Elemental planes.<br />
<br />
Nerf bards. Now.</i><hr size="1" /></blockquote>I suppose they could, but I'm not sure it'd really advance the game much. Back in the day, monks were everything, when it came to pulling, corpse dragging, scouting, yadda yadda yadda. Feign Death was VASTLY overpowered. They've gotten around this without nerfing FD specifically by adding other abilities to other characters, with some of the functionality of FD.  In particular, the stealth AA and escape for rogues, and Fading Memories for bards. <br />
<br />
I will actually agree with you that they made a mistake, though. Making fading memories based off of mana usage was a bad mistake. It takes 900 mana to do it, and a bard ONLY gets mana regen from mental clarity or Flowing Thought. With no FT, this means one Fade every 900 ticks - 90 minutes. With FT 1 (earring of the solstice), you're talking 45 minutes. Add a couple pts of mental clarity and you're at every 22.5 minutes. At these levels fading memories is nowhere near overpowered. <br />
<br />
But you've probably got a point when you're talking about an uber bard with FT 15 and MC2 or 3. At maxed mana regen, it's 19 a tick (counting 1 for breathing), which means a bard can regain the mana to fade in about 4 and a half minutes. And you're right, that probably is too powerful. I'm only up to every 9 minutes (and that recently), and it's starting to be a VERY powerful skill now that I can (almost) do it whenever I want.   Way back when the bards complained about Fade working off our SLOW mana regen, Absor told us to get some FT and deal with it. Now that the high end bards have, it might be too good an ability. <br />
<br />
Of course, some things are designed with it in mind, I think. I can't imagine how I'll ever be able to pull a Hard level LDoN dungeon (with the huge critical failure rates on lull) without fading memories and a TON of FT (I need more than I have right now). I don't have enough yet, but working on it. Of course, I don't know how ANYONE pulls hard dungeons, heh.  <br />
<br />
Of course, they've put themselves in a box now, as they've left it this way for a year and all the bards have stocked up on FT, which has virtually no other use for them, specifically because of fading memories. A nerf would have to be done very carefully or it'd really screw people over.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
