	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Originally Posted by <b>khozik</b><br /><i>Wizzys are not sustained dps.. in groups if they nuke too early they die in raids if they nuke too often they die.. </i><hr size="1" /></blockquote>You need better wizards. When you drop as much damage per nuke as a wizzie does, you don't have to nuke early to contribute some monster DPS. I'm not saying this is wrong: wizards <b>should</b> have huge damage, it's kinda what they do. However, a lot of people seem to have modern wizards confusewith their relatively gimpy Kunark/Velious era predecessors.<blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Never seen a ranger/monk/rogue leave and someone say lets get a warrior for dps.. <br />
<hr size="1" /></blockquote>People are dumb. As I implied above, tons of folks refuse to evaluate classes as they are now, not classes as they used to be. A warrior with comparable gear and AAs can do 90+% of the damage a monk dishes out. (disclaimer: late game comparison only. I don't really have a grasp on warriors pre-65 with a chunk of AAs.)<blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" /><br />
I know for a fact I can, and have in the past, kept a non elemental planes geared monk, ntov geared mostly but 120aa all defensive ones, with a 2hb from bot towers up in HOH, WITHOUT slowing the mob, and it barely straining the clerics mana.. slowed I can keep q on the guy and not even worry.. I don't think you can go 2 hours w/o a med break let alone w/o serious canni'ing action with any other class with similar gear, level and aa.. Most plate classes are meant to have high hps so they can take the damage they get, monks otoh avoid the damage all together... I can also slow the mob, nuke x2 and not take away aggro.. don't think we need to do much else.. unless you got your awesome cleric shm warrior x4 dps group going...<br />
<hr size="1" /></blockquote>I don't doubt that a shaman could keep a monk with his defensive AAs and decent gear alive in Tier 3 planes. Again, that's not that big of a deal. A shaman can keep himself alive while tanking in Tier 3 planes. It's not the <i>monk</i> that's powerful in that pair. The rest is so wrong I almost don't know where to start. This may have been true a year ago (it wasn't, but it was much closer). Parse a monk against <b>any</b> other melee class. Presupposing comparable AAs and gear, the monk will take more damage than almost any of them. I don't doubt that a shaman could keep a monk with his defensive AAs and decent gear alive in Tier 3 planes. Again, that's not that big of a deal. A shaman can keep himself alive while tanking in Tier 3 planes. It's not the <i>monk</i> that's powerful in that pair.<blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" /><br />
My opinion is monks really are very powerful, and having a 5monk 1shm group is really amazing..<hr size="1" /></blockquote>And the fact is that monks really aren't very powerful and you'd be better off with five of almost any other class in your group. That said, I still <i>enjoy</i> monk groups, they're just neither particularly efficient nor all that effective.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
