I'm sure that the whole spellbook of paladins is irrelevent, right? Sorry, paladins will still get groups because they're the most efficient back up healer. 850 hp fast group heal > 1900 hp 10 second spell single target. And I'm sure that BSS is just POINTLESS, right? Please. Warriors should have SUPERIOR aggro to Knights, our taunt skill is a mere 10 points higher but you should notice a difference in successful taunt %. We weren't even asking for that until we got absolutely pissed and stopped p'ussyfooting around. Even if Knight aggro = war aggro we'd be satisfied. If you think not being alone atop the hierarchy of aggro will make you undesireable, you're a bitch.</i><hr size="1" /></blockquote>Again, too angry to read proper english. Nowhere did I say anything about knights wanting to be alone at the top of aggro. To fill that tank slot groups want 2 basic things. HP, and aggro control. Again, Knights have only recently been able to fill those roles with the advent of PoP. If you somehow nerf the knights they cannot fulfill either of those roles. And then what good is that spellbook that you so spitefuly point out is so useful? None. Nifty heals? nope. Got a cleric for that. DPS? nope. Not even in an undead environment. Paladins of Norrath has done extensive tests on Slay undead, and proven that on average it does not add significantly to DPS. (10% IIRC) Sure Slay looks good, but it is as reliable as the procs that wars are forced to rely on to hold aggro. To do anything to Knights now is to send them back to the dark age of Kunark, where no hybrids were wanted in any group. If what knights are doing is working, why nerf them? The correct solution is to upgrade the warriors so that a warrior does a better job, but a knight can do it too. Not in a pinch, but as a viable alternative.<blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Originally Posted by <b>Thaak</b><br /><i>3) There is no doubt that taunt as a skill is broken, and if warriors are relying on that to maintain aggro, then it desperately needs to be fixed FOR THEM. I stress this point, because to just fix taunt, means that it gets fixed for every class that has it, and that gets us nowhere.<br />
