Sure it gives some more utility, but at this point, heals are still the realm of the clerics, (duids too in some cases) and we are still bringing only utility to the table, not overwhelming power.<hr size="1" /></blockquote>That's the idea behind a hybrid. They combine two or more classes' abilities for greater utility at the expense of the power that specializing in one area can offer. Sadly, it doesn't work out that way in EQ as the specialists are oftern surpassed by the generalists in the areas they are intended to excell in.<blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" /><br />
