<tr>
	<td class="alt2" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Skinned</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Lurker<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Oct 2003<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>One secret to my aggro....I'm a level 55 shadowknight, and often i pull and tank for the groups i'm in.  Now when i see warriors pull, i see them:  run to mob, hit range attack, run back.<br />
<br />
Now I on the other hand, when i pull i use this sequence:<br />
Snare with dooming darkness, 60% movement reduction snare dot<br />
Cast blood boil 500 pt dot<br />
cast spear of plauge 400 DD<br />
cast spear of disease 260 dd<br />
lifetap all the way back to the group.<br />
<br />
By then i've generated enough hate that the shaman could chain slow and not get aggro.  This is why I hold aggro easily.  Now if there is a warrior in the group, i bring the mob back, let the warrior beat on it and taunt until the mob aggro's him, then i feign death/comatose.  Then my aggro is back to zeroish, while his is what mine was +1 (taunt giving you the aggro of the highest person on the list +1)<br />
<br />
Now lately, myself, I have had paladin envy.  They are just the kings of pulling LDoN...it's alright though, they need to have a bone tossed to them sometimes.<br />
<br />
Shadowknights are just now balanced.  We've been having trouble with a couple issues, but it isn't that big of a deal, and we're generally happy with our state of things.  Paladins shouldn't get nerfed, people are just starting to like them.  Warriors need a boost though, maybe raising their offensive skill cap to give them more hits, maybe an innate proccing bonus, or an extra taunt button that doesn't give you the higher persons taunt +1, maybe a straight 100 points hate, so they can taunt, then second taunt to get a better boost on holding aggro.<br />
<br />
Please don't cry to nerf knights right after they've fixed us.  Our damage is still gimp like before, and we can still take hits almost as good as a warrior, but a warrior still gets more damage and tons more HP.  Warriors are having no trouble with mitigation of damage and have always been the best person to get hit as far as a clerics mana goes.  For a group with no cleric, a pally or SK might be a better tank, only due to the druid and shaman CH's being more on scale to their HPs as opposed warrior HPs.<br />
<br />
Classes just need to be more careful with a warrior tanking, ie:  wizards not nuking at 85%.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
