<tr>
	<td class="alt1" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Flufy</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Disciple<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Oct 2001<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>I've said it before, but perhaps unclearly, so I'll try to say it again:  Wars are specialists.  What they do, basically ALL they do, is tank mobs IN TEH FACE, as it were.  They are already the best at taking damage.  Only 9% better?  Cry me a river, my SK is busting his fat ass for tankability improvements in the 1.5% range, and those same improvements are available to Wars as well.  There is no rational argument that says that wars are being superseded as damage takers.  Whats left?  Dishing out melee damage and aggro.<br />
<br />
The fact that my SK puts out measurably more <b>weapon damage</b> than a comparably equipped war is ludicrous.  I expect to do more damage once my spells are figured in, duh, but in a weps only fight, the guy who swings swords (or clubs, in my case) part time shouldnt be surpassing the guy who does <b>just</b> that all day long.  Thats just dumb.  They should get a boost to damage done in a face-to-face confrontation, since that's what they ought to be best at, and they should get more aggro per point of damage done (or however aggro is calculated) than knights do.  Does that give them snap aggro?  No, thats what knights are for (now that they finally have a job description).  <br />
<br />
What it does do is give them stronger aggro once it's had a chance to build up.  I see zero problem with giving knights the fast aggro the have now and giving warriors strong aggro, which they dont really have now.  Increase the aggro on nukes just a little bit too, and all of a sudden the skinny dresswearing freaks are clamoring for a war tank.  Might this cause issues in bossmob/endgame encounters?  Yes.  And maybe that's where the ultimate problem lies.  <br />
<br />
If Wars are given 'strong' aggro (as a byproduct of increased face-to-face melee dps, SoE would then have to actually put some effort into 'tuning' such encounters.  The fact that they have traditionally been reluctant to do so doesnt mean that its the wrong thing to do, it just means their priorities are ****ed up*.  <br />
<br />
*(Remember, this is a company that (STILL) can't seem to fix the fact that 2hb animations got mixed up with piercing animations even though it's well known and has been going on for over two years, but they'll pay coders god knows how much money to make sure that troll chicks in Gunthak or wherever have jiggly tits.  Please.)<br />
<br />
Knights are not specialists.  By definition they are hybrids, part-timers, and the inescapable consequence of being a part-timer is that you will never be quite as good at the job as a full-timer.  <br />
<br />
<br />
Corrections, observations, critiques, and unfocused ramblings are appreciated.  Snide and inaccurate one-liners that demonstrate an inability to infer the obvious from context are not.</p>
	
	
	
