<tr>
	<td class="alt1" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Devnull</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Initiate<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Jun 2003<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Originally Posted by <b>Zorlac Sabboth</b><br /><i>- Warrior is using Vanazir, arguably one of the best weapons in the game. Monk is using some staff from a Plane of Fire mini. <---- Problem 1 with parse. You compare apples to oranges.<br />
- The parse is done tanking, Warrior is benefiniting heavily from riposte, riposte evasion AA and whatnot. <---- Problem 2 with parse.</i><hr size="1" /></blockquote>The monk would do slightly <b>less</b> damage with Vanazir than he would with Zha's. So yeah, there's a problem with the parse, but it's in the warrior's favor. <br />
<br />
The warrior is not benefitting that much from riposte damage. In the thread, Brodda quite clearly spells out exactly how much ripostes impacted each DPS set.<blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" /><br />
Now someone probably thought that if monk isn't tanking and neither is warrior, the monk will prolly do only a meager 10% more DPS with equivalent weapons and takeing out riposte AA and skill from the equation. This is quite true, warriors in my guild (similar amount of AA) with Blade of War do about same DPS as monks with the best weapons available pre time to them. <------ This is wrong, class balance issue.<hr size="1" /></blockquote>Actually, if the warrior isn't tanking then things can get really silly with /disc Offensive. On the other hand, the warrior is likely to get reduced to a grease spot on the floor of the cave if he's fighting anything nasty. The monk still has the best aggro reduction tool in the game. <blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" /><br />
What this parse shows:<br />
- Warrior is a better tank than a monk. Duh!<hr size="1" /></blockquote>True<blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" /><br />
- Warrior is doing better DPS than a monk when both tank due in part to AA/abilities AND weaker weapon. Duh!<hr size="1" /></blockquote>Not so true. Read what Brodda had to say about the apparent AA and weapon disparities. The riposte AAs helped the warrior slightly and using Zha's helped the monk slightly.<br />
<br />
Overall, the parse fairly conclusively demonstrates that the endgame monk is even weaker than many people thought. The <i>really</i> sad part is that this is a comparison to a <i>warrior</i>, another class that needs some lovin', not a class with a spell book.</p>
	
	
	
	
