<tr>
	<td class="alt2" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>SnowwSilverhammer</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Disciple<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: May 2001<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Give a Warriors two things. <br />
<br />
A New skill. Kick to the groin. (Or whatever) 1 Minute refresh + 600 Hate. No Fail.<br />
<br />
There is snap aggro Just like the incoming Stun from a paladin. Just like the Incoming CD from a Knight.<br />
<br />
And Give All Pure meele three stances. Attack defend and protection.<br />
<br />
If they have attack stance on  Thier Mana totals from gear Is worked into a formula (Even something as Simple as Mana/10 )for More attack rating. If It is to defend thier Total is worked into AC,(Again Mana/10) And if it is to protection The mana total is converted to hit points for then as long as they are protected. (Mana = Hit points)<br />
<br />
Monks under Defense stance get back Alot of the Nerf to mitagation. If not tanking they do more Damage and If they have to stay alive they can get more Hit points. Same thing for Thieves. The Defence can be when they take aggro and the damn evade is being more finiky than old grandma Jones.<br />
<br />
Knights still have aggro lock from burning Mana. So make damn fine tanks with all the utility they bring. Warriors can Have the snap aggro they need, but the Wizard that Drops The Big one 8 seconds in is going to get beat upon..<br />
<br />
And shaman Will be able to slow on incoming And not get beat down Plus it is a Fine way to keep aggro maintained in the face of the RNG being a punk.<br />
<br />
Heck make the delay 30 seconds if you want For those supposed Increadible kill speed groups. <br />
<br />
People will flip out and Say that will break the game in raids Cause the warrior will have 1000+ more Hit points... Well. So? Guilds inflated to 10+ clerics for the C heal chain, Maybe one of them can Not hot box for a change then.<br />
<br />
And of course the Warriors will roll on mana items. So? The extra Paladin would roll on it also. <br />
<br />
Verant needs to stop being head in the sand dumbasses and make the needed changes, and stop acting like sissies. Nerf the almost no mana cost Aggro boosters knights and Paladins are using to keep aggro lock and make them Actually want to use taunt now and again and suppliment with Level appropriate spells the taunt factor they use, Give warriors some form of non RNG aggo and let the damn mistakes of the last few years of item mismanagement work for everone.<br />
<br />
Or Mutter in the corner that it will all go away and classes are not that out of balance. All while friendships are being strained and morale is at an all time low because a staple of any fantasy enviroment (Warriors) are being laughed at by everyone and pitied by a few.<br />
<br />
Snoww Silverhammer Bashy Rabid Bear.. E marr</p>
	
	
	
	
	
